The KwaZulu-Natal department of co-operative (a misnomer) governance & traditional affairs successfully stopped Eskom switching off the electricity in Newcastle by launching an application in the high court. Of course, there is very little information on what this farce cost taxpayers — because we all know that the legal profession does not come cheap. It’s once again proof that our government actually cannot govern, but is adept at wasting public funds. Tony BallGillitts